(b)	The location of the diffraction minima on the screen can be deduced from the right-angled triangles.  Let positive y axis be pointed up on the screen, then we will have

	y = (50\ \text{cm})\ \tan\theta.

Denote the positions of the four minima by y_{+1}, y_{-1}, y_{+2} and y_{-2}.

	\amp y_{\pm 1} =  (50\ \text{cm})\ \tan\theta_{\pm 1} = \pm 14\ \text{cm}
	\amp y_{\pm 2} =(50\ \text{cm})\ \tan\theta_{\pm 2} = \pm 33\ \text{cm}
